						               													<description>uKloo is an educational &amp;quot;Early Reader Treasure Hunt&amp;quot; game to help teach young children reading basics. It is designed to help reluctant readers and is designed for younger ages (4+).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The goal of the game is to successfully navigate through a series of hidden clue cards to win a surprise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In uKloo, an adult puts the 'picture helper' poster on the fridge, a door, or a wall and hides a selection of clue cards around the house based on reading level and game length in such a way that the clue cards will form a chain.  The last clue is given to the players to begin the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For competitive mode, two or more chains of clues need to be created to see which child will finish first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;uKloo has been awarded Creative Child Magazine 2011 Game of the Year and is a Dr. Toy 10 Best Active Products and 100 Best Children's Products winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game box includes 42 clue cards with 3 colour-coded levels of achievement, a &amp;quot;Picture Helper&amp;quot; reference poster, 12 blank &amp;quot;Surprise&amp;quot; cards, and information about the creation of the game and future releases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
